1.	To strengthen their controls in the use of motor vehicles by complying with the provisions of COA Circular No, 77-61 and Section 361e of the Government Accounting and Auditing Manual such as issuance of pre-numbered driver’s trip tickets;
2.	Ensure proper markings of the vehicles with the name and/or logo of the Municipality with “For Official Use Only” should be made pursuant to Joint Circular No. 1 dated September 3, 1991 of the COA and DBM to prevent unauthorized use of the same;
3.	Moreover, require the driver to accomplish the Driver’s Trip Ticket, submit Monthly Report of Official Travels per vehicle summarizing in chronological order his trips for the month and also the Monthly Report of Fuel Consumption to the Auditor within the first 10 days of the ensuing month for verification purposes.

